column5: I saw this video making the rounds today. What kind of fish is this gator carrying?  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c76_b7hQXrs
looks like a redfish to me

Probably a big ole Grass Carp, they are used in many jurisdictions for vegetation control in ponds on golf courses, even in Alberta Canada still, they were legally sold and used in Ontario up until 2004 until they got lumped in with the other very undesireable Asian Carp. That is why you keep seeing fake news story about them entering the great lakes, we put them here ourselves
I was thinking grass carp too.Maybe that's how they spread from one water body to another
largemouth bass...decent one but I've caught better
